There comes a moment in every soldier’s life when the uniform feels a little heavier—not because of the medals or the stars, but because of what you’re about to leave behind.

This was that moment for me.

Handing over Command…the Final Salute from the squadron…a drive that carried years of memories, sacrifices, brotherhood and silent promises made and kept. A part of me stayed back with them that day but I walked away with something deeper—an understanding that in life, one needs to let go.

Letting go is not about forgetting. It’s about honoring what was, and making space for what will be. Even the things closest to your heart—your people, your place, your identity—must be released at some point. 

That’s not weakness. That’s life!

Change is inevitable but acceptance…that’s a choice and sometimes, saluting goodbye is the first step to embracing what’s next ⭐️ 🇮🇳 ⭐️
